-- Cimentos de Mocambique Plans to Double Output By 2011, Noticias Reports
-- Fred Katerere
-- 2010-08-03T03:41:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-03/cimentos-de-mocambique-plans-to-double-output-by-2011-noticias-reports.html

          
          
                  Aug. 3 (Bloomberg) -â€“ Cimentos de Mocambique, the largest
cement factory in Mozambique and a unit of Cimpor Cimentos de
Portugal, is set to double production by 2011, the state
controlled Noticias newspaper reported, citing Executive
Committee Chairman Steffen Kasa.  
 Cimentos de Mocambique, which plans to raise output to 1
million tons a year, has invested 18 million euros for a cement
mill to meet demand in the African nation, Noticias said.   
